Simulated training is a method of learning in which real-world scenarios are recreated in a virtual or artificial environment. It allows users to practice skills, understand systems, and make decisions without using actual equipment or facing real-world risks.

In this approach, a simulation model is designed to behave like a real system. Although the environment is not physically real, it closely mimics real conditions, enabling effective training and analysis.

In the context of the AUV sonar visualization tool, simulated training is achieved by generating artificial sonar data and displaying it in a format similar to that of real sonar systems. This helps users understand sonar operations, track objects, and interpret sensor data without requiring actual underwater equipment.


